Oct 29 2008 	Some points...	We were there for 8 days, longer then any other person that stayed there during that period. Most people appeared to only be there for two or three days.The facilities are clean, neat and well kept. The location is very good, but as you walk around the area you will note there must be 100 other places to stay with-in a few blocks.The person you deal with on-line (Harry) is not the owner, but rather the owners SIL. Harry is only there for a few hours (around lunch) most daysSomething to note is the main hotel (at least) has WiFi, but to get the WAP code you have to talk to Harry (no I'm not going to post it). The owners only (sorta) know what you are talking aboutThe owners are the &quot;grumpy&quot; couple you deal with on-site. However, I noted that the husband appears to be doing &quot;less&quot; then previous reviewers have noted. I suspect, from watching him, that his health is not as good as it was a couple years ago.The breakfasts are ample, but if you want your eggs any way except runny, expect some grumbling.	
May 6 2008 	overall excellent experience	we have stayed at the balmoral 5 different times, this being the 5th and have read all the reviews posted. first i would say, understand this is a small, family run hotel. the people cooking breakfast, cleaning the rooms and doing the check-in are on location 7 days a week for over 15 hours a day. there also maybe a slight language problem as well. so there maybe times when they seem a little gruff. that being said, if you have a bit of patience you will find them hospitable and even friendly. being american, we know first hand about impatient and demanding people. everytime we have stayed at the balmoral we've arrived during the breakfst hour. everytime we were offered breakfst before we checked in. this time breakfast had just ended and it was reopened for 4 of us. the rooms are immaculate. the beds and pillows thick and comfortable. my friend, who stayed with us for the first time and is a horrible sleeper, slept 10 hours straight ever night. yes the bathroom and shower are small[most tourist hotels are] but the water is hot and the towels plentiful and large. the breakfasts are large, hot and you are served very quickly. there tends to be a crowd around 8 am so get there earlier. the location is great. paddington station and the underground are 2 short blocks away. 3 pubs around the corner. fast food and a steakhouse within short walking distances. make your reservations thru harry, the son-in-law. he's a friendly, great guy and will get back to you almost immediately. in all, my wife and i consider the balmoral our london home. just be a little patient when checking in and you'll be pleasantly surprised.	
