Oct 27 2004	Balmoral - Outstanding London Hotel Value	The Balmoral House Hotel is a tremendous hotel value in London. It is very clean, quiet, cheerful, and the breakfast is excellent with plenty to eat. The rooms and bathrooms tend to be a bit small but that seems to be the norm in London. The staff is friendly and efficient. I have recommended it to all my friends.	
Jul 13 2004	Great Location and Price	July 2004 - We just returned from our trip to England and Ireland with our three sons (ages 16, 13, 10). We had two rooms at the Balmoral House and would definitely stay there again. The price and location are great. The Heathrow Express train arrives at Paddington Station and it's a quick walk to the hotel. The rooms are immaculately clean and the breakfast is great. The owners are pleasant and helpful. There is some good pubs and ethnic restaurants nearby (Italian, Greek and Indian) as well as a self service laundry half a block away. We paid in cash (there are several ATM's close by) to avoid the 5% extra fee with credit card. In a super expensive city such as London this hotel is a great value for the location.	
May 27 2004	Could be better	Stayed here in May 2004 and found the room to be clean and comfortable. The hosts are nice and the location is very convenient - close to the underground station and sightseeing bus stops. Yes, the bathroom was small, but I was more bothered by what seemed to be almost no water pressure in the shower. I am not sure if there are non-smoking rooms at this hotel but if you are bothered by the smell of smoke I would recommend asking. I did not ask so I am not taking points off for that. My real problem with this place was the breakfast. They stop serving breakfast at 9:00 so the small breakfast room was often very crowded after 8:30 and my last day here I ended up standing in line for a place to sit. When I did get a place, I was given toast that had been offered to someone else ten minutes earlier and was cold. The eggs had been getting more overcooked every day and that last day they were practically hard-boiled. I will probably stay someplace else next time, but if I did stay here again I would get breakfast elsewhere.	
