Jan 13 2004	Balmoral is Great	We spent 6 nights at the Balmoral House over Thanksgiving and had a very pleasant experience. The entire facility is spotless and excellently maintained. The owners are very attentive to the needs of the guests, including providing a tray of ice every night at our request. Includes an individually prepared full English Breakfast. Location is great: two blocks from Paddington, wonderful Italian restaurant (San Marcos) a block away, as is a very reasonably priced internet cafe. Only downsides: no lift (we requested and were given a room on the ground floor), bathrooms are VERY small. Also, be sure to clarify the rate you will be charged if you are going to pay by credit card. We had some miscommunication about that, although the owner resolved it in our favor as soon as we questioned it. We'll stay there again without hesitation!	
